        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 4:52PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 452 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 29 miles northwest of Roundup to 13
miles south of Ryegate, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Roundup, Ryegate, Lavina and Klein.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
